   :alt: A row of four 24dp icons and one 40dp icon
   :width: 18cm
   :align: center

--------------------------
Target size in the WCAG âœ…
--------------------------

The following is from WCAG 2.1 Success Criterion 2.5.5: Target Size (Level AAA). 
The WCAG can be difficult to understand but we will work through it to understand it and how to apply it. 
Please read the following WCAG excerpt and then answer the following questions. 

    The size of the target for pointer inputs is at least 44 by 44 CSS pixels except when:
    
    :Equivalent: The target is available through an equivalent link or control on the same page that is at least 44 by 44 CSS pixels;
    :Inline: The target is in a sentence or block of text;
    :User Agent Control: The size of the target is determined by the user agent and is not modified by the author;
    :Essential: A particular presentation of the target is essential to the information being conveyed.

.. mcq:target-size:Generally, what is the minimum target size from the WCAG?
     :At least 44 mm in height:Incorrect.
     :At least 44 CSS pixels in width:Incorrect.
     :44 by 44 mm:Incorrect.
     correct:44 by 44 CSS pixels.:That's right!

.. mcq:target-size:The headings Equivalent, Inline, User Agent Control and Essential refer to properties that pointer targets...
     :... must have to fulfil WCAG target size requirements.:Incorrect.
     :... should not ever have to fulfil WCAG target size requirements.:Incorrect.
     correct:... have when they don't need to fulfil WCAG target size requirements.:That's right!
     :... must have at least one of to fulfil WCAG target size requirements.:Incorrect.

